snippet.textDisplay: The line "Raavi to Chenab puchhdi..." has a meaning deeper than any of the Five rivers of Punjab. Makes you emotional when you imagine the five rivers as brothers and sisters separated/left behind due to partition. The eyes of my grand parents will definitely get wet after listening to this line and the line "Pende door pichhoraan(Peshawar) de". And hats off to coke studio how to brought two generations together on a platform and loved how the new generation of punjabi singing doing justice to a gem of song. Even though we have changed our getup(Maan Saab in traditional n Diljit in current) the love for punjabiyat is the same
